Appendix

Nonprofit Organizations in Los Angeles County

When asked about how data can help Program Officers and Regional Network Grantees support families in their Best Start geographies, everyone lifted up the importance of supporting local nonprofit capacity. Understanding the landscape of nonprofits in the Best Start geographies allows Program Officers and Regional Network Grantees to formulate better strategy on how to best support nonprofits and understand what local supports are missing.

Region 3

The City of Long Beach has 32,162 children age 0 to 5. The Central Long Beach Best Start Community has 9,474 children age 0 to 5, which is approximately 9% of the total population this Best Start Community.

Region 4

Nearly 700,000 Angelenos are undocumented, and 35% of the County population is foreign born.

Region 5

  • 14.6% of LA County children reported to CPS before Age 5, 5.2% of LA County children have cases substantiated before age 5, and 2.4% of LA County children enter Foster Care before age 5. Source: Childrens Data Network, Cumulative Risk of Child Protective Services Involvement.
  • Progress on this indicator helps achieve F5LA Result: Child Safety
  • This indicator is similar to and can be replaced by the Impact Frameworks Decreased rate of LA County children with Child Protective Services involvement indicator as needed.
